OL,4,CE-scooter rules too lax, says injured
OL,5,CBristol cyclist
OL,6, A Bristol cyclist injured in a crash
OL,7, with an illegally driven e-scooter is
OL,8, calling for better regulation.
OL,10,FJames Holbrook, 40, dislocated his
OL,11,Fshoulder when two girls on a private
OL,12,Felectric scooter cut across him on a
OL,13,Fcycle path in Emersons Green.
OL,15,FHe said: "I'm off work. Not only has it
OL,16,Fruined my summer but I'm also going to
OL,17,Fhave a long term injury."
OL,19,FIt is illegal for privately owned
OL,20,Fe-scooters to be driven on public land
OL,21,Fand for anyone under 18 to use them.
